- Redundant header inclusion (reduce includes)
- Frequent allocation and filling of vectors in inner loops (replace with bitmask operations)
- Recomputing pairwise subset sums every time (precompute)
- Using vector where fixed-size array is sufficient (avoid heap allocation)
- No loop unrolling, no cache optimization, no SIMD
- No Gray-code or incremental DP optimizations for subset traversal
- No attempts to reuse computations from previous iterations (could exploit subset properties)

These optimization features describe both the actual inefficiencies and missed opportunities in the program, with a focus on improving execution speed.

